    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Your method must have <code>@ResponseBody</code> and you MUST also set the correct content type Without it, browsers may display a blank page or show the raw HTML<br />\nReturn a <code>ResponseEntity&lt;Resource&gt;</code> instead.</p>\n<pre><code>@Controller\n@RequestMapping(&quot;/test&quot;)\npublic class Controller2 {\n\n    @GetMapping\n    @ResponseBody\n    public ResponseEntity&lt;Resource&gt; indexForExample() {\n        Resource resource = new ClassPathResource(&quot;templates/index.html&quot;);\n\n        return ResponseEntity\n                .ok()\n                .header(&quot;Content-Type&quot;, &quot;text/html&quot;)\n                .body(resource);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>and then you should call this http://localhost:9230/test</p>\n<p>that should be work</p>\n"
  } ],
